    public interface ITagValuesReadable
extends ITagValueIterableFromTag<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, ITagValueIteratorBindable<ListIterator<ITagValue>>, Cloneable, Serializable
    Read only interface to an ITagValues collection.

      • getFieldValue

        IValue getFieldValue(int tag)
        Retrieves the value of the first tag/value field with the given tag.

        Returns null or an IValue which is isUndefined, if no such field exists.

        Note that we could not use the simple name "getValue" for this method because it clashes with an existing method in ITagStringPairs which returns a String and we need to keep backward compatible.

        Parameters:
        tag - Tag of field to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        Value of first field with that tag.

      • getTagValues

        ITagValue[] getTagValues()
        Returns all ITagValues in the form of an array.

        Because the returned array may be reused on subsequent calls to this method (depending on the implementation) you should not assume that the number of ITagValue's equals the length of the returned array. You should scan the array from the beginning until the end of the array is reached or a null value is encountered. Also note that depending on implementation the returned array can contain undefined tag values.

        Returns:
        Array of ITagValue's. Values are terminated by a null entry or the end of the array. Never returns null.
        See Also:
        IValue.isUndefined()

      • getTagValuesSortedByTagNumber

        ITagValue[] getTagValuesSortedByTagNumber()
        Returns all ITagValues in the form of an array, sorted by the tag number of the ITagValue elements. Unlike getTagValues(), the array returned by this method will not contain undefined tag values and id not reusable, i.e. the number of ITagValue's will always equal the length of the returned array.
        Returns:
        Array of ITagValue's. Never returns null.

      • getValueAsBytes

        BytesSegment getValueAsBytes(int tag)
                      throws ConversionException,
                             MissingDataException
        Returns the bytes of the first instance of a field with the given tag.

        The BytesSegment object returned by this call can be reused by implementations of this class in subsequent calls to this method. Code using this method should not assume that calls for different tags return different BytesSegment objects. Code using this method should also not assume that the BytesSegment returned is a pristine one, that is, if you need to access the underlying byte array you should not reference the BytesSegment.bytes variable directly but use the BytesSegment.copyBytes() method instead.

        Parameters:
        tag - Tag of field to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        Value of first instance of field.
        Throws:
        ConversionException - If value cannot be converted to bytes.
        MissingDataException - If no such field exists.
        See Also:
        getValueAsBytes(int, BytesSegment)

      • getValueAsDecimal

        Decimal getValueAsDecimal(int tag)
                   throws ConversionException,
                          MissingDataException
        Returns the Decimal value of the first instance of a field with the given tag.

        Note that there is no explicit getValueAsDouble method. This method is used instead. Decimal values can be converted to double using the Decimal.doubleValue() method. Note also that you can perform arithmetic directly on Decimal objects using the methods Decimal.add(Decimal), Decimal.subtract(Decimal), Decimal.multiply(Decimal) and Decimal.divide(Decimal, int). So conversion to double (which is expensive and introduces precision issues) may not be necessary at all.

        Parameters:
        tag - Tag of field to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        Value of first instance of field.
        Throws:
        ConversionException - If value cannot be converted to Decimal.
        MissingDataException - If no such field exists.
        See Also:
        getValueAsDecimal(int, Decimal)

                          boolean defaultValue)
                   throws ConversionException
        Returns the boolean value of the first instance of a field with the given tag or defaultValue if no such field. The problem is that the representation of boolean values is not clear. In normal FIX, a boolean is represented as a character "Y" or "N".

      • isEqualTagValues

        boolean isEqualTagValues(ITagValuesReadable other,
                         boolean strictOrder)
        Compares the specified ITagValuesReadable with this ITagValuesReadable for equality, i.e. whether their contents are the same.
        Parameters:
        other - ITagValuesReadable to be compared for equality with this ITagValuesReadable.
        strictOrder - if true the order of the tags is significant, otherwise this methods returns true even if the tag order is not the same, as long as both ITagValuesReadable contain the same ITagValues
        Returns:
        true If the specified ITagValuesReadable is equal to this ITagValuesReadable.

      • indexOf

        int indexOf(ITagValue value)
        Returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified ITagValue in the list of fields, or -1 if this field list does not contain the ITagValue.

        The ITagValue comparison is done by reference, not by tag/value equality.

        This method is optional. Not all implementations support indexed operations.

        Parameters:
        value - The ITagValue to search for
        Returns:
        the index of the first occurrence of the specified ITagValue, or -1 if this field list does not contain the ITagValue
        Throws:
        UnsupportedOperationException - if the underlying implementation does not support indexed operations
